WEBVTT

00:02.299 --> 00:04.299
subtitle by peritta

00:04.300 --> 00:06.933
You're seven weeks out, Paul.
 These won't cut it.

00:06.967 --> 00:10.267
Claude pulled them from
 the last show for a reason.
 He thinks they're shit.

00:10.300 --> 00:13.400
I pulled them.
 This is my house, my name.

00:13.433 --> 00:15.533
-Are you an artist?
-No. I make princesses.

00:15.567 --> 00:18.867
CLAUDE: He knows 
 all about us.

00:18.900 --> 00:21.200
The President's office is 
 searching for a designer

00:21.233 --> 00:23.933
to dress the world,
 starting with Paris.

00:23.967 --> 00:26.833
If your next collection
fails, Monsieur Sabine,

00:26.867 --> 00:28.533
our partnership
 is effectively over

00:28.567 --> 00:30.200
and you will owe me
 everything.

00:30.233 --> 00:32.400
If he's upset about
 ten metres of velvet,

00:32.433 --> 00:34.000
we'll use 15.

00:34.033 --> 00:35.367
For some Godforsaken reason,

00:35.400 --> 00:37.533
your past was more important
 to you than your future

00:37.567 --> 00:39.567
and I had to save
 an embarrassing situation.

00:39.600 --> 00:41.267
By making it
 more embarrassing.

00:41.300 --> 00:42.833
I just wanted to go back.

00:42.867 --> 00:45.100
They didn't even
let me hold him.

00:45.133 --> 00:46.633
The adoption
will soon be formalised.

00:46.667 --> 00:49.133
God has provided a family
 that's well off

00:49.167 --> 00:52.300
and can offer this child
a future.

00:52.333 --> 00:53.733
Nina, what have you done?

00:53.767 --> 00:55.433
I heard you wanted models
 with short hair.

00:55.467 --> 00:57.533
-But you made it clear--
-I changed my mind.

00:57.567 --> 01:00.167
But I won't do it
 on a seamstress's salary.

01:00.200 --> 01:02.567
I told my friends we'd
 meet them at the restaurant.

01:03.800 --> 01:04.933
I'll... see you tomorrow.

01:04.967 --> 01:06.533
Can you think of anybody
who might

01:06.567 --> 01:09.333
judge Monsieur Sabine
 or resent him?

01:09.367 --> 01:10.967
(SCOFFS) Besides his brother.

01:11.067 --> 01:12.567
He was interested in me.

01:12.600 --> 01:15.067
-MOTHER: What does 
 he know about us? 
 -(GROANING)

01:15.067 --> 01:17.833
VICTOR: I just wanted
 to let you know
 it was taken care of.

01:17.867 --> 01:21.533
I don't need to know
 any more about it, Victor.
 Neither does Paul. Ever!

01:21.567 --> 01:23.200
-CLAUDE: What's this?
 -My castle.

01:23.233 --> 01:26.567
-Did you make it yourself?
 -No. One day it
 just showed up.

01:26.600 --> 01:27.767
This pile of rocks.

