contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

01:38.567 --> 01:41.067
* I love Paris

01:41.067 --> 01:43.567
* In the springtime

01:45.433 --> 01:47.433
* I love Paris

01:47.467 --> 01:50.533
* In the fall

01:51.800 --> 01:53.633
* I love Paris

01:53.667 --> 01:55.133
* In the winter

01:55.167 --> 01:56.667
* When it drizzles

01:57.700 --> 01:59.733
* Say, I love Paris

01:59.767 --> 02:02.600
* In the summer 
 when it sizzles *

02:02.633 --> 02:05.200
* I love Paris

02:05.233 --> 02:08.866
* Why, oh, why 
 do I love Paris? *

02:08.900 --> 02:11.067
* Because my love

02:11.067 --> 02:13.067
* Is near

02:30.200 --> 02:32.367
(CAMERA CLICKS AND WHIRS)

02:33.300 --> 02:35.100
HELEN: Oh, you made it.

02:36.100 --> 02:38.700
Lovely to see you.

02:38.733 --> 02:41.067
Thanks so much for coming.

02:47.700 --> 02:49.700
(CURTAIN IS PULLED OPEN)

02:49.733 --> 02:50.967
(FOOTSTEPS)

02:51.067 --> 02:53.267
HELEN: Can I help you
 with your coat?

02:53.300 --> 02:56.133
-Do we have enough?
 -More than enough, monsieur.

03:10.633 --> 03:12.633
(INDISTINCT CONVERSATION)

03:20.133 --> 03:22.467
-Helen.
 -Monsieur Trouvier.

03:25.333 --> 03:28.567
Where would you like me
to sit? On the radiator?

03:28.600 --> 03:30.600
I wasn't sure
 you'd be attending.

03:30.633 --> 03:33.967
My son is unveiling
 the most important
 collection of his life.

03:34.067 --> 03:35.367
Where would you
expect me to be?

03:35.400 --> 03:37.267
Some place where
you're welcome.

04:04.100 --> 04:07.933
-Where have you been?
 -In my office, drilling
 a hole in the wall...

04:07.967 --> 04:09.467
-with my forehead.
 -Nervous?

04:09.500 --> 04:14.067
No. No, if this is
 a disaster, I can
 just crawl into bed.

04:14.100 --> 04:15.933
Make it big enough for two.

04:15.967 --> 04:18.200
(BOTH CHUCKLE)

04:22.567 --> 04:24.200
(CHATTER)

04:37.700 --> 04:39.633
-(CLICKS FINGERS)
-Fire.

04:58.267 --> 05:00.667
I could move this seam.
You would still have
the long waist.

05:00.700 --> 05:02.967
I don't want to sacrifice
the keyhole in the back.

05:03.067 --> 05:05.833
I agree, monsieur,
 but as it is, this will
 require more panels.

05:05.867 --> 05:09.867
-At least a few more metres.
 -But what if we pad the hips?

05:09.900 --> 05:11.467
That would help.

05:12.500 --> 05:14.467
Can I make a suggestion?

05:14.500 --> 05:18.867
If we overlap these two
panels, we could preserve
the silhouette.

05:18.900 --> 05:21.300
But still need more material.

05:27.600 --> 05:30.500
Claude, could you
write that down, please?
Four more metres.

05:34.400 --> 05:35.967
Monsieur.

05:36.067 --> 05:39.533
You have a guest.
 Someone from Meudon.

05:39.567 --> 05:41.467
Excuse me for a moment.

05:41.500 --> 05:44.700
So, Juliette,
if we open up this and...

05:44.733 --> 05:47.400
still... have the panel...

05:47.433 --> 05:50.233
I didn't mean to sneak up
on you. Sorry.

05:59.067 --> 06:01.267
PAUL: There's no need 
 to apologise.

06:01.300 --> 06:02.700
What's this about?

06:02.733 --> 06:06.067
There's been an incident out
 at your cottage, monsieur.

06:06.100 --> 06:07.567
Would you prefer
 we speak in private?

06:07.600 --> 06:10.333
No, this is private enough,
 Inspector. Please, go on.

06:10.367 --> 06:13.833
A body has been found on the
 rear corner of your property.

06:13.867 --> 06:15.667
Buried in a shallow grave.

06:16.667 --> 06:18.100
The victim was male.

06:18.133 --> 06:20.133
He's been out there
 for over a month or so.

06:20.167 --> 06:23.067
Stabbed multiple times,
 possibly an ambush.

06:23.067 --> 06:24.933
Have you been there recently?

06:24.967 --> 06:27.467
I'm four weeks away from
showing a new collection.

06:27.500 --> 06:30.900
I'm... lucky if I make it
to my bed in Paris.

06:30.933 --> 06:34.267
(CHUCKLES)
 I see. Well, erm...

06:34.300 --> 06:36.333
...someone took advantage
of your absence

06:36.367 --> 06:39.833
and thought the kitchen
 garden would be a convenient
 place to park a dead body.

06:39.867 --> 06:41.933
Who found it?

06:41.967 --> 06:43.767
A dog.

06:43.800 --> 06:48.067
Your neighbour's child
 has been using the property
 as her playground.

06:48.100 --> 06:50.833
Your barn is her castle,
so to speak.

06:50.867 --> 06:53.933
-I'm sorry. I'm lost.
 -The corpse was her prisoner.

06:53.967 --> 06:56.500
Evidently the dog dug him up
 and, erm...

06:56.533 --> 07:00.367
the little girl
 was aware of the victim
 for a couple of days

07:00.400 --> 07:03.433
before her mother caught on.
 It's a bit gruesome,
 isn't it?

07:03.467 --> 07:06.200
One can only imagine that
the child was unaffected

07:06.233 --> 07:08.600
because of what she saw
 during the war.

07:09.467 --> 07:11.667
Do you know
 who this... victim is?

07:11.700 --> 07:14.567
We're fairly certain
 that it was a thief

07:14.600 --> 07:17.467
who'd been fleecing our town
 last year.

07:17.500 --> 07:19.933
He went missing
and must have made
the mistake of returning.

07:19.967 --> 07:22.600
Some people... (CHUCKLES)
 ...don't trust the police,

07:22.633 --> 07:24.600
and so they take matters
into their own hands.

07:24.633 --> 07:26.067
My God.

07:26.067 --> 07:28.467
Oh, please, Mr Sabine,
 I assure you

07:28.500 --> 07:31.333
that the countryside isn't
 crawling with savages.

07:31.367 --> 07:35.267
It's just that... we still
 live in a chaotic time.

07:35.300 --> 07:37.367
Is there anything I can do?

07:37.400 --> 07:41.067
Stay away from the property.
 At least for now.

07:41.933 --> 07:44.233
I may have more questions
for you.

07:44.267 --> 07:46.567
Thank you, Inspector.

07:48.667 --> 07:50.067
Mm-mm.

07:54.900 --> 07:56.333
Inspector.

07:57.600 --> 08:01.300
What do you know about this?
 Sit!

08:01.333 --> 08:02.467
Sit!

08:02.500 --> 08:04.267
(LOW CHATTER)

08:08.667 --> 08:10.167
Ugh. It smells rank.

08:10.200 --> 08:13.133
It's not a fragrance, you
 idiot, it's an astringent.

08:13.167 --> 08:15.400
Still wouldn't put that
 on my face.

08:15.433 --> 08:18.300
-It's probably goat piss.
-So what?

08:18.333 --> 08:20.400
The ancient Egyptians
 darkened their eyebrows

08:20.433 --> 08:23.333
using crocodile shit.
 Isn't that right, Nina?

08:23.367 --> 08:25.967
Uh, I've never
 heard that before.

08:26.067 --> 08:27.467
Well, you have now.

08:27.500 --> 08:30.067
But I'm sure you've known
girls who've done worse.

08:30.100 --> 08:33.433
-To attract a man, that is.
 -(GIGGLES)

08:38.567 --> 08:40.332
Where did that come from?

08:41.732 --> 08:42.900
It was a gift.

08:42.933 --> 08:44.900
Fittings are running late,
 ladies.

08:44.933 --> 08:47.500
Monsieur is delayed
 in a meeting.

08:49.233 --> 08:52.067
How are you doing? Have the
 girls made space for you?

08:52.100 --> 08:53.433
Oh, we're thrilled.

08:53.467 --> 08:56.700
Nice to have someone in here
 who can... fix a hem.

08:56.733 --> 09:01.067
She's not working
 in that department
 any more, Dominique.

09:01.067 --> 09:03.400
Take care of yourself
 in this coming month.

09:03.433 --> 09:07.167
Monsieur's given you each
 an advance on your salary.

09:07.200 --> 09:11.133
Put this towards vitamins,
 cosmetics, eating healthy,

09:11.167 --> 09:13.467
whatever it takes
 to keep you swans.

09:13.500 --> 09:15.800
Why, Charlotte,
 you flatter us.

09:15.833 --> 09:18.333
No, I don't. He does.

09:27.467 --> 09:29.800
(JAUNTY MUSIC)

09:33.533 --> 09:35.600
(WOMAN SINGS IN FRENCH)

09:38.167 --> 09:40.467
(BILLY CHATTERS)

09:53.667 --> 09:55.267
Great.

10:08.667 --> 10:12.267
I've wanted to tell you,
 I've tried to go back twice
 to the cottage,

10:12.300 --> 10:14.467
but your mother said, if that
 little girl's so mean--

10:14.500 --> 10:16.267
My mother?

10:18.500 --> 10:20.633
What does my mother
 have to do with this?

10:20.667 --> 10:22.733
She said he was going
to blackmail the family.

10:22.767 --> 10:24.300
-Who?
 -The sailor.

10:24.333 --> 10:27.000
She wanted him gone.
 She said you would too.

10:28.433 --> 10:30.667
When did my mother
 start speaking for me?

10:30.700 --> 10:33.133
She said the less you knew,
 the more we could
 protect you.

10:33.167 --> 10:36.333
You don't work for my mother!

10:44.167 --> 10:46.300
(DOOR SLAMS)

10:46.333 --> 10:48.233
Nina. What are
 you doing here?

10:48.267 --> 10:50.967
I thought you were
 in the models' cabine.

10:51.000 --> 10:54.067
Maybe...
 you want to keep this.

10:54.933 --> 10:58.567
-For luck?
 -Of course. Thank you.

11:02.900 --> 11:04.633
Well, see you at home, then.

11:10.133 --> 11:15.333
You thought this was...
 the best place to hide
 your stupid mistake?

11:16.333 --> 11:18.600
I tried.

11:18.633 --> 11:22.333
After I dropped your mother
 off, I tried different places
 to get rid of him.

11:22.367 --> 11:26.900
I almost got caught.
 Didn't know where else to go.
 There was no-one out there--

11:26.933 --> 11:29.700
Except a curious dog
and a morbid little girl.

11:32.567 --> 11:34.233
(SLAMS DESK HARD)

11:36.300 --> 11:40.067
There.
That looks lovely on you.

11:40.100 --> 11:41.833
Can we fetch Marianne?

11:41.867 --> 11:45.567
I need somebody who
 understands the mystery
 of my upper arms.

11:45.600 --> 11:48.233
She knows how to tuck them
 into my bust.

11:48.267 --> 11:50.433
I'll see if she can pop down.

11:51.567 --> 11:53.500
(FOOTSTEPS RETREAT)

11:57.367 --> 11:59.600
Ohhh!

11:59.633 --> 12:02.667
Look what your genius
 made for me.

12:02.700 --> 12:05.200
I'd hug you but one of these
 pins might draw blood.

12:05.233 --> 12:07.900
I didn't know you were here.
 I would have packed enough
 for three.

12:07.933 --> 12:11.300
No, no, no, no. No, no,
 I'm not eating this month.

12:12.567 --> 12:16.133
Neither is Paul.
 I haven't seen him for days.

12:16.167 --> 12:20.267
You can't come up
 with something like this
 by putting in bankers' hours.

12:20.300 --> 12:22.233
At least you married somebody
 who works.

12:22.267 --> 12:25.267
My last one just wanted
 an allowance for the track.

12:25.300 --> 12:28.533
Now, is there anything
 in here we can drink.

12:31.567 --> 12:32.767
Oh.

12:32.800 --> 12:38.867
Well, I'm sorry.
I didn't realise this was
more than a meal.

12:38.900 --> 12:42.633
Doesn't matter.
 I don't think it would have
 made much of an impact.

12:43.833 --> 12:46.333
The others haven't.

12:49.100 --> 12:51.233
(TAP RUNNING)

12:53.067 --> 12:55.633
-(EXHALES)
 -Who was the visitor?

12:55.667 --> 12:57.800
Police officer from Meudon.

12:57.833 --> 12:59.800
Why did he want
to speak to you?

13:01.067 --> 13:03.167
A property line dispute
 out at the cottage.

13:03.200 --> 13:05.333
When was the last time
 you spoke to Maman?

13:05.367 --> 13:08.200
Er... this morning.
 I gave her a key to my flat.

13:08.233 --> 13:09.800
She can look after the cat.

13:13.067 --> 13:15.300
He's been sick.

13:22.067 --> 13:26.800
He says that it's about...
 this perfume deal.

13:26.833 --> 13:28.533
But I think
 it's something else.

13:30.067 --> 13:31.733
It's like we're living
in two different worlds.

13:31.767 --> 13:33.500
Well, you are.

13:33.533 --> 13:35.100
They're called male
 and female.

13:35.133 --> 13:36.467
(CHUCKLES)

13:36.500 --> 13:38.400
I've had husbands from
 three different continents

13:38.433 --> 13:43.600
and they have all
 needed to feel like
 they were in charge.

13:44.433 --> 13:46.833
And you know how I did it?

13:46.867 --> 13:50.133
By wearing shoes
with lousy heels.

13:50.167 --> 13:55.400
What? What are you talking
 about? You don't own shoes
 with lousy heels.

13:55.433 --> 13:57.400
The hell I don't.

13:57.433 --> 13:59.067
I always wear them
 on the second date

13:59.100 --> 14:01.967
and I find the perfect kerb
 to fall off,

14:02.067 --> 14:05.433
so they can catch me
 and feel strong.

14:10.067 --> 14:13.233
You've just gotta fall off
 a kerb, honey.

14:16.500 --> 14:17.767
I just...

14:17.800 --> 14:21.600
I think it's a little late
 for a second date.

14:21.633 --> 14:24.200
Marjorie, it's been
 eight years.

14:24.233 --> 14:26.800
-I want to be his partner.
 -And you can be.

14:26.833 --> 14:28.533
You can.

14:29.367 --> 14:31.967
You just gotta be
smart about it.

14:32.067 --> 14:33.833
Do it quietly.

14:33.867 --> 14:36.200
(DOOR OPENS)

14:37.667 --> 14:39.533
-Helen.
 -Uh-oh.

14:39.567 --> 14:43.733
I asked for Marianne and I
 got you. Have you come down
 here to cut off my sleeves?

14:43.767 --> 14:45.867
Hello, Marjorie.

14:45.900 --> 14:48.400
-I brought you some supper.
 -Hmm.

14:48.433 --> 14:51.367
How thoughtful. Unfortunately
 I don't have time.

14:51.400 --> 14:54.467
I'll enjoy it when I get back
 from my meeting.

14:56.333 --> 14:58.633
-Ah, Charlotte.
 -Monsieur, your car is ready.

14:58.667 --> 15:00.367
Victor is waiting for you.

15:00.400 --> 15:03.067
Place those invoices on my
 desk so I can look at them
 when I get back.

15:03.100 --> 15:05.133
You know, I can't breathe
in this thing. It's...

15:05.167 --> 15:07.533
cutting off my circulation.
 Help me, will you?

15:07.567 --> 15:09.200
(INDISTINCT CONVERSATION)

15:13.767 --> 15:15.700
(GIRLS GIGGLE)

15:28.533 --> 15:30.667
-(THUD)
-(GASPS)

15:32.800 --> 15:34.700
(GASPS)

15:34.733 --> 15:36.133
I expected King Kong.

15:36.167 --> 15:38.467
And it turns out it's...
Fay Wray.

15:38.500 --> 15:42.700
(CLEARS THROAT) I'm sorry.
 I didn't mean to disturb you.

15:42.733 --> 15:44.067
Or Paris.

15:44.100 --> 15:46.700
(CHUCKLES) We're, uh...
 tougher than we look.

15:48.267 --> 15:50.400
Nina, wait. Can I...?

15:50.433 --> 15:53.067
Can I, uh...
Can I show you something?

15:53.067 --> 15:56.333
I've been asked to do
 a visual record
 of the collection's progress.

15:56.367 --> 16:00.067
Sort of a countdown
 to curtain. And I got
 this beauty of your ma.

16:06.933 --> 16:09.533
She can sit like that
 for hours.

16:11.600 --> 16:13.600
Let me see the others.

16:16.533 --> 16:19.300
A nice one of Monsieur.

16:19.333 --> 16:21.600
(CHUCKLES) I'm not sure how
 Eloise will feel about this.

16:21.633 --> 16:25.133
But at least her mop
 is slim and elegant.

16:27.967 --> 16:31.167
And that's about as best
I could do of Claude.

16:32.067 --> 16:33.633
He's a little camera shy.

16:34.867 --> 16:36.700
Got any idea why?

16:39.633 --> 16:41.733
He's supposed to be
 the manager, right?

16:42.733 --> 16:44.567
He is.
He's Monsieur's brother.

16:44.600 --> 16:46.367
Maybe that's the problem.

16:47.233 --> 16:49.300
I've got a brother myself.

16:49.333 --> 16:53.100
He saw combat while I sorted
 maps behind a desk.

16:53.133 --> 16:55.267
He resents
 the hell out of me for it.

16:55.300 --> 16:57.167
Monsieur does not
resent Claude.

16:58.767 --> 17:04.133
-Does that work both ways?
 -Who put this in your head?
 Dominique?

17:04.166 --> 17:07.099
I don't need anybody
 to tell me what I see
 with my own eyes.

17:07.133 --> 17:09.599
But you need someone
 to tell you the truth.

17:09.633 --> 17:11.967
Monsieur worked very hard
to get where he is.

17:12.067 --> 17:15.467
His brother looks up to him.
 And they treat the rest of us
 like family.

17:15.500 --> 17:17.599
But you're choosing
 to spend time with someone

17:17.633 --> 17:19.467
who's more closely related
 to reptiles.

17:22.433 --> 17:24.599
Nina...

17:24.633 --> 17:27.567
Dominique and I, we've been
 to a few clubs, some cafés.

17:27.599 --> 17:29.100
She's introduced me
 to her friends.

17:29.133 --> 17:31.100
Then why are you
 bringing me the gift?

17:32.067 --> 17:34.200
There are many girls
 in Paris.

17:34.233 --> 17:37.167
You'll go broke giving
all of us gifts, GI Joe.

17:38.233 --> 17:40.567
We don't exist
 for your pleasure.

17:51.733 --> 17:53.467
(CAT MEOWS)

17:58.100 --> 18:00.467
(DOOR OPENS)

18:03.333 --> 18:05.767
How many people does it take
 to feed a cat?

18:05.800 --> 18:08.067
-I came here to see you.
-What's wrong?

18:08.067 --> 18:09.800
You're wrong.

18:11.433 --> 18:13.200
I have some news.

18:14.533 --> 18:16.700
I don't know what your cards
 tell you,

18:16.733 --> 18:18.267
but this might be
your lucky day.

18:18.300 --> 18:21.500
I've spoken to Victor...
and the police...

18:21.533 --> 18:25.500
who think that fellow he
 buried... on my property...

18:25.533 --> 18:29.300
is a local thief,
 and not a friend of your son.

18:31.167 --> 18:32.500
Paul, let me explain.

18:32.533 --> 18:35.367
You're more desperate and
dangerous than I thought.

18:35.400 --> 18:38.067
-You should be thanking me.
 -For what?

18:38.100 --> 18:40.233
Putting everything
 I've worked for,

18:40.267 --> 18:42.100
our entire future,
 in jeopardy?

18:42.133 --> 18:46.200
You were already in jeopardy.
 He knew too much
 about the war.

18:46.233 --> 18:49.167
There was no other choice.
 He knew the truth about you.

18:49.200 --> 18:51.533
He knew Claude
was the one that matters.

18:51.567 --> 18:55.900
All he had to do was open his
 big trap to the wrong person.

18:55.933 --> 18:59.267
-The one that matters?
 -You know what
 I'm talking about.

19:00.633 --> 19:02.100
What I know is that...

19:02.133 --> 19:04.167
from this point on,
 you're done.

19:05.500 --> 19:10.067
You do nothing... nothing
 without consulting me first.

19:10.100 --> 19:12.433
If your soup needs salt,
you ask me how much.

19:12.467 --> 19:15.367
You need to piss, you hold it
 till I tell you to let it go.

19:15.400 --> 19:17.367
You're done making decisions

19:17.400 --> 19:20.400
that affect anyone else in
 this family. Is that clear?

19:22.067 --> 19:24.300
Who the hell do you think
you're talking to?

19:26.600 --> 19:28.700
(SHE GASPS)

19:28.733 --> 19:32.567
Do you want me to tell Claude
 who you really are?

19:32.600 --> 19:35.467
Because I will. I will!

19:42.500 --> 19:45.567
Who's gonna protect him
 when I'm gone?

19:47.300 --> 19:50.667
It's my fault
 he's the way he is.

19:50.700 --> 19:54.067
You have a wife. He has
 no-one. And he never will.

19:54.100 --> 19:56.200
Claude will do just fine
without you.

19:57.767 --> 20:00.567
We all will.

20:00.600 --> 20:02.833
(DOOR OPENS)

20:02.867 --> 20:04.800
(DOOR SLAMS SHUT)

20:04.833 --> 20:06.733
(EXCITED CHATTER)

20:16.267 --> 20:17.867
What about the wedding dress?

20:17.900 --> 20:19.067
What about it?

20:19.100 --> 20:21.400
-Has Monsieur decided--
 -He hasn't.

20:21.433 --> 20:22.733
MODEL: Ow!

20:24.867 --> 20:27.167
Anyone got pins?
I need pins now!

21:09.233 --> 21:11.300
Stop walking on clouds.

21:11.333 --> 21:14.767
You've got to be
a cloud walking.

21:14.800 --> 21:16.467
Look, try...

21:17.867 --> 21:19.267
Try these.

21:20.933 --> 21:22.533
Try again.

21:24.233 --> 21:27.400
What you need to do,
 you need to pretend
 it's Sunday.

21:28.733 --> 21:32.167
You've got nowhere to go
and you've got all day
to get there.

21:32.200 --> 21:35.067
Now try again. Go.

21:37.500 --> 21:39.267
Take your time,
 take your time!

21:39.300 --> 21:41.233
What did I just say?
 Take your time.

21:41.267 --> 21:43.367
If it were Sunday,
 I'd be sleeping.

21:44.233 --> 21:46.700
-(SIGHS)
 -Oh, what?

21:46.733 --> 21:50.167
This was a mistake. I don't
 want to disappoint Monsieur.

21:50.200 --> 21:52.400
You won't! Besides,
you shouldn't be worrying
about that.

21:52.433 --> 21:54.967
He couldn't walk in those
heels at gunpoint.

21:55.067 --> 21:58.500
Stay there and...
 put your shoes back on.

22:04.233 --> 22:05.800
(GENTLE ORCHESTRAL MUSIC)

22:05.833 --> 22:08.200
OK. Up!

22:09.567 --> 22:11.567
Stay still, stay still.

22:12.567 --> 22:14.333
Try again.

22:20.133 --> 22:21.533
Watch me, watch me.

22:21.567 --> 22:23.067
(MAN SINGS IN FRENCH)

22:28.767 --> 22:30.967
The dress follows you.

22:31.067 --> 22:33.167
You don't follow the dress.

22:34.067 --> 22:36.067
Turn around.

22:42.333 --> 22:44.667
(LAUGHS) That's it.
 That's it. That's it.

22:44.700 --> 22:46.267
That's it.

22:46.300 --> 22:48.233
(LAUGHS)

22:49.233 --> 22:50.367
(LAUGHS)

22:50.400 --> 22:52.700
* BIZET:
 Habanera aria from Carmen

23:06.300 --> 23:08.467
And turn.

23:15.767 --> 23:18.567
Come towards me. That's it.

23:18.600 --> 23:20.633
Just keep walking.

23:20.667 --> 23:22.600
Don't.

23:25.667 --> 23:27.667
* CHARLES TRENET: Hop! Hop!

24:00.400 --> 24:02.667
* The Blue Danube Waltz

24:37.733 --> 24:40.100
(GASPS)

24:43.400 --> 24:44.900
-(TURNS RADIO OFF)
 -Please, don't...

24:44.933 --> 24:48.600
-Don't stop cos of me.
 -I should get home.

24:48.633 --> 24:51.633
Nina, I thought a lot about
 what you said that day,

24:51.667 --> 24:55.533
you know, upstairs and...

24:55.567 --> 24:57.500
I was out of line.

24:57.533 --> 25:01.400
I put you in an awkward
 position and I'm...
 I'm sorry.

25:03.667 --> 25:06.067
And I should have said that
 weeks ago, but, you know...

25:06.067 --> 25:09.333
it's just... it's been
 so crazy around here.

25:09.367 --> 25:11.600
I don't even remember
 what I said.

25:13.200 --> 25:17.067
I do. And, um...
and you were right. I...

25:18.267 --> 25:21.267
You are not here
 for my... pleasure.

25:25.133 --> 25:27.900
But it is a pleasure...
 to see a girl

25:27.933 --> 25:31.133
who once said that these
 dresses were for other people

25:31.167 --> 25:33.567
looking... so...

25:34.767 --> 25:37.100
...comfortable in them now.

25:39.067 --> 25:41.067
(LIGHT CLICKS)

25:41.067 --> 25:44.067
Oh, sorry. I'll...
 do the stairs... again.

25:44.067 --> 25:46.367
Oh, no. Eloise,
 please come in.

25:46.400 --> 25:48.567
It's fine.

25:50.700 --> 25:52.467
I was just leaving.

26:00.500 --> 26:01.867
(BIRDSONG)

26:01.900 --> 26:03.800
(LEAVES RUSTLING)

26:05.900 --> 26:08.400
I'd like to try to cover
this clasp.

26:08.433 --> 26:10.200
(LOW CHATTER)

26:21.067 --> 26:22.733
(WHISPERS)

26:28.633 --> 26:30.267
Take a spin round the floor.

26:30.300 --> 26:33.367
-Monsieur Gambon. I wish--
 -I was in the neighbourhood.

26:33.400 --> 26:35.800
I thought I'd stop by
 and give my regards.

26:35.833 --> 26:40.100
I should have realised you'd
 have scant time for a social
 call the week of your show.

26:40.133 --> 26:42.233
So, are you ready
for an audience?

26:42.267 --> 26:45.667
We will be.
 Will you be joining us?

26:45.700 --> 26:47.100
I'll try my best.

26:47.133 --> 26:50.400
And what about
 Monsieur Trouvier?

26:50.433 --> 26:51.867
He'll be here.

26:51.900 --> 26:53.433
If he's asked.

26:53.467 --> 26:55.900
So this wasn't a social call?

26:55.933 --> 26:59.300
We have a lot invested
 in this partnership working

26:59.333 --> 27:02.200
and it would be
a frightful embarrassment
to the President

27:02.233 --> 27:03.867
and all parties involved

27:03.900 --> 27:06.767
if Monsieur Trouvier
 felt himself excluded
 from the debut.

27:06.800 --> 27:08.567
He's been invited.

27:08.600 --> 27:11.333
But my silent partner has
 remained silent for weeks.

27:11.367 --> 27:15.067
I'm not quite sure
 if he's hoping for me
 to succeed or fail.

27:15.067 --> 27:17.200
Well, then, let me
 enlighten you.

27:17.233 --> 27:20.433
I dined with him last night
 and he seemed
 quite enthusiastic

27:20.467 --> 27:22.800
about the work
 of another designer.

27:24.367 --> 27:26.667
Then you've answered
 my question.

27:26.700 --> 27:28.567
It's not too late.

27:28.600 --> 27:31.067
Just make sure your partner's
 given a choice seat.

27:31.067 --> 27:33.600
Pardon. Monsieur,
 you have a phone call.

27:33.633 --> 27:34.867
They said it's urgent.

27:34.900 --> 27:37.733
Please, take it. Not to
 worry. I'll let myself out.

27:37.767 --> 27:39.533
I let myself in.

27:40.933 --> 27:42.733
I'll see you on Friday, then.

27:47.533 --> 27:49.600
What is this about?
 My mother?

27:49.633 --> 27:51.333
Someone called Bompard.

27:52.667 --> 27:54.433
He said he's a detective.

27:57.800 --> 27:59.633
Billy?

28:04.433 --> 28:05.667
Billy?

28:05.700 --> 28:07.633
(PIGEONS COOING)

28:30.867 --> 28:32.767
PAUL: I'm sorry. 
 I'm confused.

28:32.800 --> 28:36.067
Are you saying that the man
 you thought was dead
 and buried is still alive?

28:36.067 --> 28:40.633
Apparently he was arrested
 last night at the
 train station in Lyon.

28:40.667 --> 28:42.433
I see.

28:44.600 --> 28:47.833
So, do you know
who it is that was found
on my property?

28:47.867 --> 28:50.300
Not yet but... we will.

28:50.333 --> 28:53.433
Which will require us
 re-opening the investigation.

28:53.467 --> 28:55.933
-I'm sorry to trouble you. 
 -No, it's no trouble.

28:55.967 --> 28:58.133
If I can be of any help,
please let me know.

28:58.167 --> 29:02.067
We'll need to see the 
 documents from when 
 you bought the house.

29:03.633 --> 29:05.400
I'll forward them to you.

29:05.433 --> 29:08.800
Well, it might be better 
 to deliver them yourself.

29:08.833 --> 29:12.467
It would be helpful to meet
 there. At the property.

29:12.500 --> 29:14.967
Have you any time
this afternoon?

29:15.067 --> 29:17.267
Say, erm... three o'clock?

29:19.333 --> 29:21.200
-I'll make the time.
 -Thank you.

29:21.233 --> 29:24.100
-See you then.
 -Bye.

29:24.133 --> 29:26.600
(HANGS UP RECEIVER)

29:26.633 --> 29:28.267
I'll bring the car around.

29:28.300 --> 29:29.800
No.

29:30.867 --> 29:33.800
No. You'll stay here.

29:33.833 --> 29:35.567
I'll drive myself.

29:36.600 --> 29:38.733
You've done enough.

29:44.067 --> 29:46.067
(LIFT RUMBLES)

29:48.133 --> 29:50.267
(DOORS CLUNK OPEN)

29:52.100 --> 29:54.267
(LOW MUSIC AND CHATTER)

30:04.400 --> 30:08.133
-May I?
 -What are you doing?

30:08.167 --> 30:10.333
It's not how Monsieur
 designed it.

30:39.667 --> 30:41.367
(DOOR CLOSES)

30:41.400 --> 30:43.333
HELEN: Hello.

30:43.367 --> 30:46.067
What are you doing here
in the middle of the day?

30:46.100 --> 30:47.967
I had to find some papers.

30:48.000 --> 30:49.767
How was lunch with Marjorie?

30:49.800 --> 30:53.300
Well, if you ever need a new
 press agent, she's your girl.

30:53.333 --> 30:56.033
Is there anyone
she doesn't know?

30:56.067 --> 30:58.567
Her connections may
 come in handy some day.

30:58.600 --> 31:00.333
That day is Friday.

31:01.167 --> 31:04.200
Wait. Papers? For what?

31:04.233 --> 31:08.133
Hm? Oh, there's a situation
 out at the cottage.

31:08.167 --> 31:12.367
A property line dispute.
I've got to go out there.

31:12.400 --> 31:13.633
Now?

31:13.667 --> 31:16.133
They're practically setting
 up chairs in the salon.

31:16.167 --> 31:17.833
They need you here.

31:17.867 --> 31:20.900
Here, give them to me.
 I'll take them.
 Victor can drive me.

31:20.933 --> 31:22.600
No!

31:22.633 --> 31:25.700
Thank you...
 I'll take care of it.

31:32.100 --> 31:34.433
Why are you going
to the cottage?

31:36.733 --> 31:39.333
Just tell me the truth.

31:40.200 --> 31:43.167
The truth is...
I am overwhelmed.

31:43.200 --> 31:46.300
I don't need you to become
 an additional burden.

31:47.733 --> 31:51.233
I'm not a burden.
I'm your wife.

31:52.933 --> 31:55.300
What's going on?

32:02.100 --> 32:04.533
My mother killed that sailor.

32:11.300 --> 32:13.667
I already knew that.

32:15.633 --> 32:18.267
How would you know that?

32:18.300 --> 32:21.467
Let's just say I had my
 suspicions and you just...

32:22.767 --> 32:24.367
...confirmed it.

32:33.233 --> 32:35.067
What are you gonna do now?

32:35.067 --> 32:40.200
I give this detective the
paperwork he's asked for.

32:40.233 --> 32:42.367
Then I'll figure
something out.

32:43.533 --> 32:46.067
Does Claude know?

32:46.067 --> 32:48.233
Please, don't tell him,
 Helen.

32:56.133 --> 32:57.700
Will you do that for me?

33:00.167 --> 33:04.100
Please promise me
he'll never know.

33:28.567 --> 33:31.600
I'm confused.
 Where am I in all this?

33:31.633 --> 33:34.700
I see a lovely spot reserved
 for the other Madame Sabine

33:34.733 --> 33:37.167
but I... I seem to be
 among the missing.

33:37.200 --> 33:39.533
It's still a work in
 progress, madame.

33:39.567 --> 33:41.533
That's why I did it
 in pencil.

33:41.567 --> 33:43.567
Some guests haven't even
responded yet.

33:43.600 --> 33:45.833
Well, here's my response.
I'll be here.

33:45.867 --> 33:50.133
And I'd like my chair to have
 four legs and a back.

33:50.167 --> 33:53.700
I'll certainly pass that on
 to Monsieur.

33:55.333 --> 33:57.767
He's lucky to have you,
 Charlotte.

33:57.800 --> 34:02.367
My son's always gravitated
 towards sharp,
 talented women.

34:02.400 --> 34:04.833
Most men
 find that threatening.

34:04.867 --> 34:07.533
God knows
 I scared off enough.

34:07.567 --> 34:09.667
I bet you have, too.

34:11.067 --> 34:14.067
I've little time to think
of anything but my work.

34:15.167 --> 34:17.600
Good for you. It'll pay off.

34:17.632 --> 34:20.233
I've a good feeling
 about this collection.

34:20.266 --> 34:21.567
Do you?

34:21.600 --> 34:22.900
Oh, yes.

34:22.933 --> 34:25.433
It's in the cards.

34:25.467 --> 34:27.199
Excuse me.

34:34.300 --> 34:36.100
What was their reaction?

34:36.132 --> 34:38.266
-Who?
-The other girls.

34:38.300 --> 34:41.266
When they found out Monsieur
 picked you to be the bride.

34:41.300 --> 34:43.467
Juliette, have you taken
your break yet?

34:43.500 --> 34:45.533
You're functioning
 on very little sleep.

34:45.567 --> 34:47.100
I... I'm nearly done.

34:47.132 --> 34:48.800
I've got it from here. Go.

34:48.833 --> 34:50.367
Eat something.

34:56.199 --> 34:58.300
Have you taken a break?

34:58.333 --> 35:00.467
I don't need a break.

35:00.500 --> 35:02.533
I need this dress
to be perfect.

35:02.567 --> 35:05.067
If you leave it pinned, Mama,
 I could finish the stitching.

35:05.067 --> 35:06.733
That's not a terrible idea.

35:06.767 --> 35:10.767
At least I'd know
 what you were doing
 with your free time.

35:10.800 --> 35:13.100
What does that mean?

35:13.133 --> 35:14.700
What were you thinking?

35:14.733 --> 35:17.633
Sending a donation like that
 to a novice?

35:17.667 --> 35:19.333
What were you after, Nina?

35:19.367 --> 35:22.433
I wanted her to know that
 I was earning more money now.

35:22.467 --> 35:24.233
-That I was in
 a better place.
 -No.

35:24.267 --> 35:26.567
You wanted to bribe her
 for information.

35:26.600 --> 35:28.767
Which only shows how naive
 and foolish you still are.

35:28.800 --> 35:30.833
It wasn't a bribe.

35:30.867 --> 35:33.333
And, anyway, it's none
 of your business.

35:34.333 --> 35:35.767
Really?

35:37.267 --> 35:40.100
Then why was this addressed
 to me and not to you?

35:48.133 --> 35:51.500
-Where's the money?
 -I'll hold on to that.

35:51.533 --> 35:54.400
You don't think things
 through, Nina.

35:55.733 --> 36:00.433
It's my money. I earned it.
 And I want it back.

36:00.467 --> 36:03.267
That child already belongs
 to someone else.

36:03.300 --> 36:06.400
You can't buy back
 what's no longer yours.

36:06.433 --> 36:09.067
And why would you
even want to?

36:09.067 --> 36:12.167
Do you want this,
your costume,

36:12.200 --> 36:14.800
or something that you might
 really wear one day?

36:14.833 --> 36:17.700
No man is interested in
 raising someone else's child.

36:17.733 --> 36:19.200
Think about your future.

36:19.233 --> 36:22.333
I don't know
 what my future holds.

36:22.367 --> 36:25.300
But if you don't start
 letting me make
 my own decisions,

36:25.333 --> 36:28.067
it's not going
 to include you.

36:37.567 --> 36:41.933
Can you think of anyone
 who might want to compromise
 your reputation?

36:41.967 --> 36:45.667
Anyone in particular
 with whom you've had
 a negative encounter

36:45.700 --> 36:48.067
in the last six months?

36:48.067 --> 36:51.900
Inspector, I'm days away
 from what could be
 a turning point in my career.

36:51.933 --> 36:54.867
There may be more
 than one person who'd relish
 my fall from grace.

36:54.900 --> 36:58.233
But I have no personal idea
 of who that might be.

36:58.267 --> 37:00.233
Oh, it sounds like
 quite an event.

37:01.300 --> 37:03.567
Could there be
 an extra seat for me?

37:10.500 --> 37:12.500
(LOW CHATTER)

37:14.567 --> 37:18.367
That was quite a break.
 What did you do?

37:18.400 --> 37:19.967
Roast a hen?

37:20.067 --> 37:23.100
-I was only gone for 15--
-Were you asleep
when you stitched this?

37:23.133 --> 37:24.533
I used the navy thread
 so it--

37:24.567 --> 37:27.433
I don't give a damn about
 the colour. It's about pride.

37:27.467 --> 37:28.833
Workmanship.

37:28.867 --> 37:30.667
We are not sewing flour bags.

37:30.700 --> 37:32.567
-Let me do it over.
 -This isn't a school!

37:32.600 --> 37:36.167
We don't have time to correct
 your stupid foolish mistakes!

37:37.767 --> 37:41.100
What are you looking at?
 Is that panel finished yet?

37:41.133 --> 37:43.300
Go to work!

38:04.733 --> 38:06.467
(DOOR OPENS)

38:06.500 --> 38:07.633
Oh.

38:07.667 --> 38:10.367
Didn't expect you to be back
 until tomorrow.

38:10.400 --> 38:13.233
-What's that?
 -A source of conflict.

38:13.267 --> 38:15.067
I have three different
 seating charts

38:15.067 --> 38:18.533
and your mother wants to be
 front and centre
 on every one of them.

38:18.567 --> 38:21.300
She also insisted
 on trying on the same suit

38:21.333 --> 38:23.300
that Marjorie plans on
 wearing to the show.

38:23.333 --> 38:26.233
And did you tell her
 that suit and that seat
 were already taken?

38:26.267 --> 38:29.367
I tried, but she insists on
 wearing black and white.

38:29.400 --> 38:31.433
She says,
 "It's in the cards."

38:33.767 --> 38:35.367
Will you join me?

38:36.667 --> 38:38.267
Thank you.

38:46.300 --> 38:49.533
If we locked Marjorie and my
 mother in the same room
 with one dress,

38:49.567 --> 38:53.100
who do you think
 would come out wearing it?

38:53.133 --> 38:56.633
I think Marjorie would have
 the top half and your mother
 would have the bottom.

38:56.667 --> 38:58.867
(BOTH CHUCKLE)

38:58.900 --> 39:01.100
Mm.

39:07.533 --> 39:09.167
(CLEARS THROAT)

39:12.067 --> 39:14.967
It won't matter
 where anyone sits.

39:15.067 --> 39:18.833
This show is going to be
 brilliant from every angle.

39:18.867 --> 39:21.800
If we can just make it
 to the show.

39:21.833 --> 39:24.200
-Is everything all right?
-Hm?

39:24.233 --> 39:27.100
-With that detective?
 -Oh, that.

39:27.133 --> 39:31.367
It's all taken care of. It
 was just a misunderstanding.
 I've cleared it up.

39:31.400 --> 39:33.100
Good.

39:34.667 --> 39:36.233
But, you know...

39:37.300 --> 39:39.500
...if I can ever
be helpful...

39:40.867 --> 39:42.367
...don't hesitate to ask.

40:43.000 --> 40:45.233
(FLOURISH OF JAZZ)

40:50.933 --> 40:52.767
(CHATTER)

40:58.200 --> 41:01.333
Nearly every seat's taken,
 so we should start soon.

41:02.867 --> 41:06.067
Do you still want to speak
 to the staff before we begin?

41:14.867 --> 41:17.067
(CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKS)

41:21.933 --> 41:23.467
BILLY: Helen.

41:39.467 --> 41:41.500
MOTHER:
 Is there room up here for me?

41:42.600 --> 41:44.300
Why would you
 want to be up here?

41:44.333 --> 41:47.267
This is exactly where
I always imagined I'd be,
my darling.

41:47.300 --> 41:49.333
Right at your side.

41:49.367 --> 41:52.700
-Well, let me get you a seat.
 -No, I'll be fine, really.

41:54.400 --> 41:56.067
How's the cat?

41:56.067 --> 41:58.067
Er... much better.

41:58.067 --> 42:00.700
He only vomits now
when I mention your name.

42:00.733 --> 42:02.200
Lovely.

42:38.467 --> 42:41.533
(GROANS) I can't breathe!
Can you loosen it?

42:41.567 --> 42:45.300
Tighten it. That'll teach you
 to make fun of my goat piss.

42:47.167 --> 42:49.067
BILLY: Turn your shoulder...

42:50.767 --> 42:53.800
Sorry, Nina. Could you
 just hold that for me?
 That's beautiful.

42:53.833 --> 42:56.533
Just look to me.

42:57.833 --> 42:59.800
That's really nice.

43:02.067 --> 43:04.567
(CHATTER)

43:17.400 --> 43:20.500
Claude, your brother wants
 to say something to us.

43:20.533 --> 43:22.167
Upstairs.

43:25.067 --> 43:28.300
Everyone upstairs.
Monsieur wants to speak.

43:32.633 --> 43:34.567
Hurry! Move! (CLAPS HANDS)

43:34.600 --> 43:36.233
Nina, Billy.

43:36.267 --> 43:39.767
Come on, everyone.
 Up we go, up we go.

43:39.800 --> 43:43.067
Dominique, please, hurry.
Monique.

44:14.933 --> 44:18.133
For the past eight weeks, 
 we've kept the lights 
 burning late

44:18.167 --> 44:20.500
and the shutters
tightly closed,

44:20.533 --> 44:23.067
so that nothing
 would distract us.

44:23.067 --> 44:26.400
No-one could look
 over our shoulders.

44:26.433 --> 44:29.233
Today we open the shutters
 and share the work.

44:30.400 --> 44:35.600
We aim for perfection
 and pray that we come close.

44:35.633 --> 44:40.867
Every one of you
 has made enormous sacrifices
 to get us here.

44:40.900 --> 44:43.367
I hope you feel
 that it wasn't in vain.

44:44.767 --> 44:46.467
I certainly don't.

44:48.967 --> 44:50.567
I salute you.

44:54.200 --> 44:57.967
-To the collection.
 -ALL: The collection.

44:58.067 --> 45:00.133
* Quizás, Quizás, Quizás

45:27.700 --> 45:30.600
MARJORIE:
 You have to have that one.

46:04.067 --> 46:06.067
(MURMURING)

46:09.300 --> 46:11.733
Sorry.

46:22.400 --> 46:24.100
(LOW CHATTER)

46:41.100 --> 46:43.400
Beautiful frock.

46:53.667 --> 46:56.100
-How do you like that?
 -Wow. It's brilliant.

46:57.800 --> 47:00.567
WOMAN: Look at the size
 of her waist. Look at that.

47:21.067 --> 47:22.533
Looks like it's flown here.

47:51.167 --> 47:54.100
(MURMURING AND GASPS)

47:57.133 --> 47:59.233
MAN: Ohhhh!

48:05.067 --> 48:06.300
Ohhh.

48:17.533 --> 48:20.833
Beautiful. Look at that.

48:20.867 --> 48:24.467
(QUIETLY) Holy fuck.
 I wanna be buried in that.

48:30.167 --> 48:33.567
Hey. My gloves. Take them,
 take them. Take them!

48:36.667 --> 48:38.433
(SNIFFS) What's that smell?

48:40.800 --> 48:42.300
(GASPS) The dress!

48:42.333 --> 48:45.267
Call someone!
 Get Monsieur Sabine!

48:45.300 --> 48:46.633
(PANICKED SHOUTING)

48:48.400 --> 48:49.800
Oh, my goodness!

48:52.333 --> 48:56.067
-BILLY: What happened?
 -Unplug your lamp.

48:56.067 --> 48:59.067
That dress was nowhere
 near my lamp. I wouldn't have
 put that there.

48:59.067 --> 49:01.933
-Who moved the rack?
-How did this happen?
-Doesn't matter. It did.

49:01.967 --> 49:04.100
-What are you doing?
 -Just close the door.

49:04.133 --> 49:06.233
-Close it!
 -Carry on.

49:06.267 --> 49:09.267
PAUL: Leave it alone. We'll
 end with something else.

49:09.300 --> 49:11.267
-The dress burned.
 -I don't know how
 it happened.

49:11.300 --> 49:14.900
-We don't need a bride--
 -You close with the bride!

49:14.933 --> 49:16.767
Flor, Dominique,
go out again.

49:16.800 --> 49:19.067
-But they've already seen--
 -A second look, together.

49:19.100 --> 49:21.233
-I need tulle--
 -You have to hide--

49:21.267 --> 49:23.400
-I've got this!
 -At least let me help you.

49:24.533 --> 49:26.067
Another in the back.

49:26.067 --> 49:28.467
-What about the silhouette?
 -It'll be the same
 as the front.

49:28.500 --> 49:29.667
Hurry!

49:30.833 --> 49:32.167
Scissors.

49:32.200 --> 49:34.967
Everybody keep moving.
 You're in a show.

49:35.067 --> 49:37.367
Can you hide all that?
 Claude?

49:37.400 --> 49:40.567
Nina, you should get changed.
 Can somebody help her?
 Please!

49:47.200 --> 49:50.933
Ohhh, stop!
 Take it from the petticoat.

49:50.967 --> 49:55.367
-PAUL: What are we gonna do?
 -I can hide this in the fold.
 -Claude...

49:55.400 --> 49:58.133
-Just get me the scissors.
 -Here.

49:58.167 --> 50:00.767
I'll tack it back to the...
 Hold this piece.

50:04.067 --> 50:05.467
This will work.

50:06.633 --> 50:07.800
Here. Lace.

50:27.933 --> 50:30.100
(GASPS AND MURMURS)

51:28.700 --> 51:30.467
MARJORIE: Bravo!

51:30.500 --> 51:32.067
Bravo!

51:32.100 --> 51:33.933
(APPLAUSE)

51:33.967 --> 51:35.167
MARJORIE: Bravo!

51:35.200 --> 51:37.200
CROWD: Bravo!

51:42.800 --> 51:44.567
Bravo!

51:48.700 --> 51:52.567
Thank you. Thank you.

51:52.600 --> 51:54.500
-Bravo!
 -Bravo!

52:19.533 --> 52:22.067
MARJORIE: How about that?

52:40.967 --> 52:43.133
(APPLAUSE CONTINUES)

52:46.667 --> 52:48.667
(CHEERING)

52:56.100 --> 52:58.267
(JAUNTY TUNE)

53:07.933 --> 53:10.067
No, thanks.

53:10.067 --> 53:11.800
(POP)

53:13.367 --> 53:15.633
PAUL: You're a natural.
 Have fun.

53:17.900 --> 53:21.267
-Monsieur Trouvier
 seemed impressed.
 -A little shocked.

53:21.300 --> 53:24.733
-Ah...
 -Congratulations...

53:24.767 --> 53:29.167
Ashes and gloom are over,
darling. Romance is back.

53:29.200 --> 53:31.633
Now, Mr Sabine
 has given us a new look

53:31.667 --> 53:34.367
and I'm sure as hell
 ready to wear it. (LAUGHS)

53:34.400 --> 53:37.600
-You can write that down.
-MAN: So what exactly
inspired you?

53:37.633 --> 53:41.067
I'd like to say that it all
 starts with the sleeve,
 monsieur,

53:41.067 --> 53:42.733
but I'm afraid
 it's just not true.

53:42.767 --> 53:45.900
It starts with the type of
 woman you want to design for.

53:45.933 --> 53:48.067
You certainly found
 your muse.

53:48.967 --> 53:51.167
No, the muse is my wife.

53:58.267 --> 54:00.700
-Where's Claude?
-I don't know.

54:00.733 --> 54:04.800
I hope, wherever he is,
 he's celebrating, too.

54:04.833 --> 54:06.967
CLAUDE: So won't your 
 lady friend be missing you?

54:07.067 --> 54:10.633
No. She has other things
to distract her.

54:11.667 --> 54:14.100
Champagne, gossip...

54:14.933 --> 54:17.467
...free food.

54:17.500 --> 54:20.833
And should she come looking
 for you, do you have a name?

54:20.867 --> 54:22.700
Cesar.

54:22.733 --> 54:24.367
You?

54:25.600 --> 54:27.267
Claude.

54:28.933 --> 54:31.067
What's this?

54:34.700 --> 54:36.767
I don't recall
 seeing this one.

54:40.067 --> 54:42.400
That's because
 you were looking at me.

55:12.200 --> 55:14.433
(PIANO MUSIC)

55:16.633 --> 55:18.300
(CHAMPAGNE CORK POPS)

55:19.600 --> 55:21.200
Who are they?

55:21.233 --> 55:23.100
I beg your pardon?

55:23.133 --> 55:26.433
The tardy couple who nearly
 missed the first dress.
 How do we know them?

55:26.467 --> 55:28.533
I don't.

55:37.867 --> 55:39.300
Monsieur.

55:43.367 --> 55:45.567
I didn't know
 you were still here.

55:45.600 --> 55:48.200
I... wanted to talk
 to Nina but...

55:48.233 --> 55:51.667
there's so many people around
 her, I thought I'd wait.

55:51.700 --> 55:54.400
Monsieur has invited her
to a small after-party.

55:54.433 --> 55:57.300
Right. Of course.

55:57.333 --> 56:00.067
Well, I'll see her
 on Monday, then.

56:00.100 --> 56:02.233
If you still want me
 to come in.

56:02.267 --> 56:04.167
You'd better be here.

56:04.200 --> 56:06.333
The real work
 is about to begin.

56:08.067 --> 56:10.367
We'll be doing Nina's work,
 too.

56:11.667 --> 56:13.567
It's just us, now, Juliette.

56:21.267 --> 56:23.500
Can I walk to the metro
 with you?

56:25.133 --> 56:27.267
Yes, I'd like that.

56:29.700 --> 56:30.867
Jules.

56:30.900 --> 56:33.633
Ah. Just the man
I'm looking for.

56:34.467 --> 56:37.100
-You were looking for me?
-Yes.

56:37.133 --> 56:39.133
I wanted to speak to you
in private

56:39.167 --> 56:44.367
but I wouldn't dare interrupt
 your legion of admirers.

56:44.400 --> 56:46.533
Excuse me.

56:48.133 --> 56:49.900
Are you one of them?

56:49.933 --> 56:53.700
Well, let's see
 if all this enthusiasm

56:53.733 --> 56:56.200
translates to sales, hm?

56:56.233 --> 56:58.533
Enjoy your moments.

56:58.567 --> 57:01.267
They never get as good
 as this again.

57:02.233 --> 57:05.300
We'll talk soon. Hm?

57:23.767 --> 57:26.767
Ah. So you're out here.

57:30.567 --> 57:33.800
So that could have gone
 either way, huh?

57:33.833 --> 57:36.500
The wedding dress.

57:36.533 --> 57:40.800
I guess that's what separates
 mere dressmakers
 from Paul Sabine.

57:56.667 --> 58:00.733
I never properly thanked you.
 For the lovely card.

58:00.767 --> 58:03.067
(SCOFFS) Oh, please.
 That was nothing.

58:06.500 --> 58:09.533
Why, uh... Vivien Leigh?

58:09.567 --> 58:14.567
I mean, there's a lot
of beautiful movie stars.

58:14.600 --> 58:18.500
A few of them were downstairs
 tonight, admiring you.

58:18.533 --> 58:23.067
-What is it about her--
 -She has fire in her eyes.

58:23.067 --> 58:25.767
But she's not willing to
admit when she's afraid.

58:29.500 --> 58:32.467
Are you? Afraid?

58:37.567 --> 58:39.600
I know I am. (CHUCKLES)

58:41.133 --> 58:43.533
Once the master finds out

58:43.567 --> 58:47.667
that it was my light that
torched that dress, uh...

58:47.700 --> 58:49.933
...I'm guessing my days here
 are pretty much numbered.

58:49.967 --> 58:52.200
It was an accident.

58:52.233 --> 58:54.233
It was a pricy one.

58:54.267 --> 58:56.333
About two months' wages.

58:57.667 --> 59:00.067
I'll leave Paris owing him.

59:04.267 --> 59:08.833
I don't know. Maybe
everything happens for
a reason, though, right?

59:08.867 --> 59:12.133
I didn't know
 what I was looking for
 when I came here but...

59:14.667 --> 59:17.067
...I certainly know
 what I'm leaving with.

59:19.800 --> 59:22.067
I should be thanking you.

01:00:04.567 --> 01:00:06.567
(SHE SIGHS)

01:00:13.900 --> 01:00:15.767
(CAR ENGINE IDLES)

01:00:20.400 --> 01:00:24.133
I need to tell you something.
 But not here.

01:00:25.000 --> 01:00:26.900
Has Monsieur Sabine sent you?

01:00:26.933 --> 01:00:28.567
No.

01:00:28.600 --> 01:00:30.433
Come on. Get in.

01:00:31.700 --> 01:00:33.000
(DOOR SLAMS SHUT)

01:00:33.033 --> 01:00:35.233
(KEYS RATTLE)

01:00:37.000 --> 01:00:39.167
(CAT MEOWS)

01:00:52.933 --> 01:00:55.033
(THUNDER RUMBLES)

